node.text:
A word from our Co-Founder & Co-CEO @colleenwachob: I wrote an introduction for a post earlier in the year on why we were removing the word “infertile” from our library of content on mindbodygreen. A colleague kindly pointed out that the word “miscarriage" used in the post was not very empowering or emphathetic for women who have lost pregnancies. As someone who has personally lost pregnancies, I couldn’t agree more. 

We are always growing on our wellness journey and the language that we use will continue to evolve. The word "miscarriage" fails us because it implies that we, and our bodies, did something wrong and carried our children incorrectly. We have become so accustomed to the use of the word “miscarriage” that it’s hard to realize the ways it fuels guilt. 

mindbodygreen has updated our library of content to remove the word “miscarriage” and use “pregnancy loss.” To help understand the complexity of this language, we’re fortunate to have scientist + fertility specialist, @doctor_cleopatra to talk us through the research. We hope Dr. C’s words in this video resonate with you or a loved one in a similar way they did with our family.

node.title: A Fertility Expert on The Impact of The Word “Miscarriage"

A word from our Co-Founder & Co-CEO @ColleenWachob: At mindbodygreen, we champion the mind-body connection. It’s the foundation from which we build our well-being. What’s more, the language we use matters—especially when it comes to our health.

After many conversations with doctors and fertility experts, mindbodygreen is changing how we use the word “infertility” on our website. Where we’ve misused it in the past, we’ve removed the term. Going forward, we’ll delineate between those struggling with fertility, and those diagnosed with true sterility. To help understand the complexity of this language, we’re fortunate to have scientist + fertility specialist, @doctor_cleopatra to talk us through the research. We hope Dr. C’s words in this video resonate with you or a loved one in a similar way they did with our family.

While removing the “in” prefix may seem simply semantic to some people, we feel strongly about this change. Our hope at mbg is that anyone who reads a story about fertility on our site feels empowered by information, and never discouraged by disheartening labels.

#mindbodygreen #hormones #womenshealth #fertility #fertilityjourney #mentalhealth

node.title: A Fertility Expert on The Impact of The Word “Infertility”

Join @ChefSerenaPoon to make her go-to No Bake Superfood Cookies. 🍪 See below for ingredients: - 1/2cupcoconut sugar - 2 TB unsweetened nut milk - 3 TB coconut oil
- 2 TB cacao powder - 1/3 C shredded coconut
- 2 TB raw hemp seeds
- 2 TB raw pumpkin seeds
- 1 C rolled oats
- 1/3 C nut butter - 1/2 tsp vanilla extract - 1 pinch sea salt - 2 TB chopped raw pistachios
